      "stem_html": "<p>Which of the following pairs of structures represent resonance forms, and which do not? Explain.</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa0lRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--09848d5bd08dd3aca1f0fe1ddce3145a36126041/OChem_02_06_012a.jpg\" alt=\"Chemical structures of phenylmethylium on the left and 1-methylenecyclohexa-2,5-dien-4-ylium on the right.\">\n<b>(b)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa01RIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a3906e7a326c649d79a89500b4e5a08533f471a6/OChem_02_06_012b.jpg\" alt=\"Chemical structures of 2-methyl-4-ethylhexa-1,3-diene on the left and 2-ethyl-4-methylpenta-1,3-diene on the right.\"></p>",
